Description:
START ME UP
Looking for your first home or maybe adding to your investment portfolio?
This gorgeous Federation style townhouse is located at the front of the block in this quiet pocket of Keilor Village. Offering downstairs bedroom, huge lounge, well equipped kitchen, dining and laundry. Upstairs further two bedrooms and bathroom complete with bath and shower. Outside we have a single garage with access through to north facing sunny rear courtyard. Includes BIRs, gas ducted heating, cooling, dishwasher and much more. Walking distance to schools, Village shops and local sporting facilities. With further cosmetic attention this one certainly has a great future.

Description:
FAMILY STYLE WITH PARKLAND BACKDROP
Impressively spacious and versatile, this two-level home presents a ready-to-enjoy lifestyle opportunity complete with poolside entertaining area and instant access to Calder Rise Neighbourhood Park. Beyond its attractive rendered facade, the home's free-flowing design boasts four bedrooms (large downstairs master with WIR and stylish ensuite), main family bathroom and guest powder room (third WC). Add to this a large formal lounge through to the light-filled open living/dining area with gas-coal fireplace and well-appointed granite-top kitchen. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, polished hardwood floors, rumpus/retreat (upstairs), excellent storage options throughout, double garage (remote-controlled) with internal entry, plus undercover entertaining area, backyard with in-ground pool and direct access to the park. A quiet and convenient location, it's close to public transport and easy freeway access, choice of local schools, as well as Keilor Village shops and eateries. Land approx 543sqm. Ready to move in and enjoy!

Description:
FOR FAMILIES THAT LOVE TO ENTERTAIN...
Beyond its immaculate front garden and rendered facade, this three-level home delivers an outstanding indoor/outdoor family lifestyle in a prized Keilor Village location. Set on a wide elevated block, the home's tastefully enhanced interior boasts four generous bedrooms (master with WIR and modern ensuite), main bathroom with spa, home office/study, light-filled lounge, open living/dining area and contemporary-style kitchen with glass splashbacks and stainless steel appliances. Add to this a family sized laundry/third WC, rumpus/billiard room, sauna and dedicated theatre room. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, additional split-system a/c (living area), excellent storage options, 2.1kW solar power system, double garage (remote-controlled) with internal entry, plus an expansive backyard garden complete with large undercover entertaining deck and heated in-ground pool. Set well back from the street (service road), it's walking distance to shops and eateries, public transport, schools and parks, easy access to the Calder Freeway. Land approx 634sqm.

Description:
Masterfully Renovated For Modern Living
Completely renovated and beautifully presented, this three-bedroom plus study home offers fabulous family living in a pleasant street close to parks, transport, Keilor Village and schools. The tasteful living domain leads out to an elevated and covered entertainer's deck, featuring a terrific barbecue and overlooking the rear garden where you'll find a healthy lawn that kids will love. Superbly finished, the kitchen shows off Blanco stainless steel appliances including a five-burner gas cooktop with fish and wok burners, electric oven and canopy rangehood, plus stone surfaces, a dishwasher, pantry, appliance cupboard and soft-close drawers. Under a soaring ceiling with exposed beams, the dining domain invites you to enjoy delicious meals. Bedrooms each have a mirrored built-in robe or a walk-in robe, plus the master offers a fully tiled ensuite. Further inclusions comprise a chic fully tiled main bathroom, central vacuum, ducted heating, split system cooling, polished floorboards, front garden with watering system, electronic garage and enormous storage.

Description:
Luxury, Grandeur, Elegance
Instantly imparting a strong impression of excellence, this three-bedroom plus study/fourth bedroom contemporary residence has been superbly designed and constructed with first-class features throughout with no expense spared.
Immaculately maintained, the home boasts lavish window dressings, high ceilings, rosettes and double glazing, creating a peaceful environment.
The relaxed layout provides a lounge and open plan adjoining area comprising a sitting area, gourmet kitchen and dining, from which the inviting entertainer's courtyard beckons.
A 900mm stainless steel Smeg oven combines with a canopy rangehood, dishwasher, expansive stone benches, glass splashbacks and two-pack quality cabinetry in the kitchen.
Two of the very comfortable bedrooms offer walk-in robes and the third provides a mirrored built-in robe.
Fully tiled bathrooms include the main bathroom and a spa ensuite with a frameless shower, toilet and stone-topped vanity, and a powder room is desirably positioned on the ground floor.
Ducted heating, refrigerated cooling, alarm system, video intercom, remote controlled garage and extra off-street parking unite to ensure outstanding comfort, security and convenience.
On the 476 bus route and a stroll to Taylors Lakes Shopping Centre and Taylors Creek walking/cycling trail, you'll also be only a short drive to freeway access, schools and lively Watergardens shops, restaurants and cinemas.
Features
- Immediately impressive, with superior inclusions and quality finishes
- Private rear position as one of only two residences
- Premium Smeg kitchen appliances including 900mm Smeg oven, and stone surfaces throughout
- Alarm, video intercom, ducted vacuum, double glazing, central heating and refrigerated cooling
- Automatic garage with safe entry and second off-street parking space
- Stroll to transport, shopping centre and Taylors Creek trail; short drive to schools and freeway

Description:
Family Haven in Park Precinct
Quality positioned in a cul-de-sac with sweeping and undisturbed views of Brimbank National Park, this family haven demands attention.
A gentle evolution over the years has created a warm and welcoming Four bedroom family residence situated within walking distance to the beautiful Keilor Village and its noted caf's, entry to prestigious local schools and access to Melbourne's CBD within a 16km direct route.
The home itself comprises of sumptuous corbel featured kitchen with European appliances, distinguished formal sitting and dining area opening out to the opulent outdoor entertaining area featuring a family in ground heated pool to use all year round. Description:
BIG BLOCK, AMAZING VIEWS AND VILLAGE PRESTIGE
With its versatile design, expansive gardens and spectacular valley outlook, this distinctive two-level home presents a terrific opportunity to secure your family's future in sought-after Keilor Village. Immediately comfortable with scope to modernize, the home's free-flowing interior comprises three generous bedrooms (all with robes), master ensuite and main bathroom (spa), kitchen/meals with dishwasher and ample cupboards space, open-plan living/dining area leading out to a wide entertaining balcony to enjoy the views over Brimbank Park and Maribyrnong River. Other features of the home include a separate lounge/rumpus area complete with bar, ducted heating and evaporative cooling, wood heater (living area), big laundry and under-stair storeroom, plus double carport via gated driveway, private front garden and leafy backyard with direct access to reserve and river trails. Also close to village shops and cafes, local schools, public transport and easy freeway access. Land approx 847sqm.

Description:
ONE OF KEILOR'S FINEST MODERN HOMES
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSE FRIDAY 17 APRIL AT 6PM
A statement in luxury living, this architect-designed masterpiece delivers an indoor/outdoor environment of absolute quality, style and family flexibility on approx 1121sqm of land. With towering ceilings and the finest fittings and materials throughout, the home's expansive floorplan boasts a large master bedroom with fitted walk-in robe and deluxe ensuite, three further bedrooms (one with ensuite, all with BIRs) and study/5BR, main bathroom and guest powder room, dedicated theatre room complete with tiered flooring, lounge with gas-log fireplace, vast open-plan living/dining area and gourmet stone-top kitchen with breakfast bar. Add to this a large laundry and internal access into the two double garages (remote-controlled) via electric-gated driveways. Other stand-out features include Daikin integrated heating/refrigerated cooling, ducted vacuum, motorized blinds, C-bus automation, and so much more, plus a north-facing outdoor area complete with al-fresco entertaining deck, outdoor kitchen/BBQ, in-ground pool and spa, studio, gym, sauna and additional (fourth) bathroom. Close to Keilor Village shops and eateries, local parks, schools, public transport and easy freeway access.

Description:
AMAZING SPACE IN A PRIZED VILLAGE LOCALE
Set on a huge double block, this expansive single-level home offers a ready-made indoor/outdoor family lifestyle ideally situated in the heart of Keilor Village. Beyond its distinctive facade, the home's versatile design highlights four bedrooms (large master with WIR, spa ensuite and private courtyard), study, second ensuite and main family bathroom, multiple living zones with formal lounge/dining (complete with wet-bar), superb granite-bench kitchen with stainless steel appliances and adjoining meals area, as well as a vast living/entertaining room. Other features include ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, full-size laundry, excellent storage options, plus outdoor entertaining deck with motorized awning overlooking the in-ground pool, north-facing backyard and double garage. Walking distance to village shops and cafes, it's also close to Keilor Primary School, parks and sporting facilities, public transport and easy freeway access. Land approx 30.45m x 37.8m - 1152sqm. What an opportunity!
